Use the standard library
This is how to string_xor of a and b:
   Remember that n is a's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Remember that result is ""
   Do this n times:
      Remember that ca is item i in a
      Remember that cb is item i in b
      Remember that x is "0"
      When ca is not cb, then:
         Remember that x is "1"
      End when
      Add result to x
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> string_xor of "010" and "110" 
"100"
>>> string_xor of "111000" and "101010" 
"010010"
>>> string_xor of "1" and "1" 
"0"